{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"One of the most common ways of dividing the world"},{"time":3000,"text":"is into those who believe"},{"time":5000,"text":"and those who don't --"},{"time":7000,"text":"into the religious and the atheists."},{"time":10000,"text":"And for the last decade or so,"},{"time":12000,"text":"it's been quite clear"},{"time":14000,"text":"what being an atheist means."},{"time":16000,"text":"There have been some very vocal atheists"},{"time":19000,"text":"who've pointed out,"},{"time":21000,"text":"not just that religion is wrong,"},{"time":23000,"text":"but that it's ridiculous."},{"time":25000,"text":"These people, many of whom have lived in North Oxford,"},{"time":28000,"text":"have argued --"},{"time":30000,"text":"they've argued that believing in God"},{"time":33000,"text":"is akin to believing in fairies"},{"time":35000,"text":"and essentially that the whole thing"},{"time":37000,"text":"is a childish game."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39000,"text":"Now I think it's too easy."},{"time":41000,"text":"I think it's too easy"},{"time":43000,"text":"to dismiss the whole of religion that way."},{"time":46000,"text":"And it's as easy as shooting fish in a barrel."},{"time":48000,"text":"And what I'd like to inaugurate today"},{"time":50000,"text":"is a new way of being an atheist --"},{"time":52000,"text":"if you like, a new version of atheism"},{"time":55000,"text":"we could call Atheism 2.0."},{"time":58000,"text":"Now what is Atheism 2.0?"},{"time":60000,"text":"Well it starts from a very basic premise:"},{"time":62000,"text":"of course, there's no God."},{"time":65000,"text":"Of course, there are no deities or supernatural spirits"},{"time":68000,"text":"or angels, etc."},{"time":70000,"text":"Now let's move on; that's not the end of the story,"},{"time":73000,"text":"that's the very, very beginning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76000,"text":"I'm interested in the kind of constituency"},{"time":79000,"text":"that thinks something along these lines:"},{"time":81000,"text":"that thinks, \"I can't believe in any of this stuff."},{"time":83000,"text":"I can't believe in the doctrines."},{"time":86000,"text":"I don't think these doctrines are right."},{"time":88000,"text":"But,\" a very important but, \"I love Christmas carols."},{"time":92000,"text":"I really like the art of Mantegna."},{"time":95000,"text":"I really like looking at old churches."},{"time":97000,"text":"I really like turning the pages of the Old Testament.\""},{"time":100000,"text":"Whatever it may be,"},{"time":102000,"text":"you know the kind of thing I'm talking about --"},{"time":104000,"text":"people who are attracted to the ritualistic side,"},{"time":106000,"text":"the moralistic, communal side of religion,"},{"time":109000,"text":"but can't bear the doctrine."},{"time":111000,"text":"Until now, these people have faced a rather unpleasant choice."},{"time":114000,"text":"It's almost as though either you accept the doctrine"},{"time":117000,"text":"and then you can have all the nice stuff,"},{"time":119000,"text":"or you reject the doctrine and"},{"time":121000,"text":"you're living in some kind of spiritual wasteland"},{"time":123000,"text":"under the guidance of CNN and Walmart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125000,"text":"So that's a sort of tough choice."},{"time":127000,"text":"I don't think we have to make that choice."},{"time":129000,"text":"I think there is an alternative."},{"time":131000,"text":"I think there are ways --"},{"time":133000,"text":"and I'm being both very respectful and completely impious --"},{"time":136000,"text":"of stealing from religions."},{"time":138000,"text":"If you don't believe in a religion,"},{"time":140000,"text":"there's nothing wrong with picking and mixing,"},{"time":142000,"text":"with taking out the best sides of religion."},{"time":145000,"text":"And for me, atheism 2.0"},{"time":147000,"text":"is about both, as I say,"},{"time":149000,"text":"a respectful and an impious way"},{"time":152000,"text":"of going through religions and saying, \"What here could we use?\""},{"time":155000,"text":"The secular world is full of holes."},{"time":157000,"text":"We have secularized badly, I would argue."},{"time":160000,"text":"And a thorough study of religion"},{"time":162000,"text":"could give us all sorts of insights"},{"time":164000,"text":"into areas of life that are not going too well."},{"time":167000,"text":"And I'd like to run through a few of these today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171000,"text":"I'd like to kick off by looking at education."},{"time":174000,"text":"Now education is a field"},{"time":176000,"text":"the secular world really believes in."},{"time":178000,"text":"When we think about how we're going to make the world a better place,"},{"time":180000,"text":"we think education; that's where we put a lot of money."},{"time":183000,"text":"Education is going to give us, not only commercial skills, industrial skills,"},{"time":186000,"text":"it's also going to make us better people."},{"time":188000,"text":"You know the kind of thing a commencement address is, and graduation ceremonies,"},{"time":191000,"text":"those lyrical claims"},{"time":193000,"text":"that education, the process of education -- particularly higher education --"},{"time":196000,"text":"will make us into nobler and better human beings."},{"time":199000,"text":"That's a lovely idea."},{"time":201000,"text":"Interesting where it came from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203000,"text":"In the early 19th century,"},{"time":205000,"text":"church attendance in Western Europe"},{"time":207000,"text":"started sliding down very, very sharply, and people panicked."},{"time":210000,"text":"They asked themselves the following question."},{"time":212000,"text":"They said, where are people going to find the morality,"},{"time":215000,"text":"where are they going to find guidance,"},{"time":217000,"text":"and where are they going to find sources of consolation?"},{"time":219000,"text":"And influential voices came up with one answer."},{"time":221000,"text":"They said culture."},{"time":223000,"text":"It's to culture that we should look"},{"time":225000,"text":"for guidance, for consolation, for morality."},{"time":228000,"text":"Let's look to the plays of Shakespeare,"},{"time":230000,"text":"the dialogues of Plato, the novels of Jane Austen."},{"time":233000,"text":"In there, we'll find a lot of the truths"},{"time":235000,"text":"that we might previously have found in the Gospel of Saint John."},{"time":238000,"text":"Now I think that's a very beautiful idea and a very true idea."},{"time":241000,"text":"They wanted to replace scripture with culture."},{"time":244000,"text":"And that's a very plausible idea."},{"time":246000,"text":"It's also an idea that we have forgotten."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250000,"text":"If you went to a top university --"},{"time":252000,"text":"let's say you went to Harvard or Oxford or Cambridge --"},{"time":254000,"text":"and you said, \"I've come here"},{"time":256000,"text":"because I'm in search of morality, guidance and consolation;"},{"time":258000,"text":"I want to know how to live,\""},{"time":260000,"text":"they would show you the way to the insane asylum."},{"time":263000,"text":"This is simply not what our grandest and best institutes of higher learning"},{"time":266000,"text":"are in the business of."},{"time":268000,"text":"Why? They don't think we need it."},{"time":270000,"text":"They don't think we are in an urgent need of assistance."},{"time":273000,"text":"They see us as adults, rational adults."},{"time":275000,"text":"What we need is information."},{"time":277000,"text":"We need data, we don't need help."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279000,"text":"Now religions start from a very different place indeed."},{"time":282000,"text":"All religions, all major religions,"},{"time":284000,"text":"at various points call us children."},{"time":287000,"text":"And like children,"},{"time":289000,"text":"they believe that we are in severe need of assistance."},{"time":291000,"text":"We're only just holding it together."},{"time":293000,"text":"Perhaps this is just me, maybe you."},{"time":295000,"text":"But anyway, we're only just holding it together."},{"time":298000,"text":"And we need help. Of course, we need help."},{"time":300000,"text":"And so we need guidance and we need didactic learning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303000,"text":"You know, in the 18th century in the U.K.,"},{"time":305000,"text":"the greatest preacher, greatest religious preacher, was a man called John Wesley,"},{"time":308000,"text":"who went up and down this country delivering sermons,"},{"time":311000,"text":"advising people how they could live."},{"time":313000,"text":"He delivered sermons on the duties of parents to their children"},{"time":315000,"text":"and children to their parents,"},{"time":317000,"text":"the duties of the rich to the poor and the poor to the rich."},{"time":319000,"text":"He was trying to tell people how they should live"},{"time":321000,"text":"through the medium of sermons,"},{"time":323000,"text":"the classic medium of delivery of religions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326000,"text":"Now we've given up with the idea of sermons."},{"time":328000,"text":"If you said to a modern liberal individualist,"},{"time":330000,"text":"\"Hey, how about a sermon?\""},{"time":332000,"text":"they'd go, \"No, no. I don't need one of those."},{"time":334000,"text":"I'm an independent, individual person.\""},{"time":336000,"text":"What's the difference between a sermon"},{"time":338000,"text":"and our modern, secular mode of delivery, the lecture?"},{"time":341000,"text":"Well a sermon wants to change your life"},{"time":344000,"text":"and a lecture wants to give you a bit of information."},{"time":347000,"text":"And I think we need to get back to that sermon tradition."},{"time":350000,"text":"The tradition of sermonizing is hugely valuable,"},{"time":352000,"text":"because we are in need of guidance,"},{"time":354000,"text":"morality and consolation --"},{"time":356000,"text":"and religions know that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358000,"text":"Another point about education:"},{"time":360000,"text":"we tend to believe in the modern secular world"},{"time":362000,"text":"that if you tell someone something once, they'll remember it."},{"time":365000,"text":"Sit them in a classroom, tell them about Plato"},{"time":367000,"text":"at the age of 20, send them out for a career in management consultancy for 40 years,"},{"time":370000,"text":"and that lesson will stick with them."},{"time":372000,"text":"Religions go, \"Nonsense."},{"time":374000,"text":"You need to keep repeating the lesson 10 times a day."},{"time":377000,"text":"So get on your knees and repeat it.\""},{"time":379000,"text":"That's what all religions tell us:"},{"time":381000,"text":"\"Get on you knees and repeat it 10 or 20 or 15 times a day.\""},{"time":384000,"text":"Otherwise our minds are like sieves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386000,"text":"So religions are cultures of repetition."},{"time":388000,"text":"They circle the great truths again and again and again."},{"time":390000,"text":"We associate repetition with boredom."},{"time":392000,"text":"\"Give us the new,\" we're always saying."},{"time":394000,"text":"\"The new is better than the old.\""},{"time":396000,"text":"If I said to you, \"Okay, we're not going to have new TED."},{"time":398000,"text":"We're just going to run through all the old ones"},{"time":400000,"text":"and watch them five times because they're so true."},{"time":402000,"text":"We're going to watch Elizabeth Gilbert five times"},{"time":405000,"text":"because what she says is so clever,\" you'd feel cheated."},{"time":408000,"text":"Not so if you're adopting a religious mindset."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"The other things that religions do"},{"time":412000,"text":"is to arrange time."},{"time":414000,"text":"All the major religions give us calendars."},{"time":416000,"text":"What is a calendar?"},{"time":418000,"text":"A calendar is a way of making sure that across the year"},{"time":421000,"text":"you will bump into certain very important ideas."},{"time":424000,"text":"In the Catholic chronology, Catholic calendar,"},{"time":427000,"text":"at the end of March you will think about St. Jerome"},{"time":429000,"text":"and his qualities of humility and goodness"},{"time":431000,"text":"and his generosity to the poor."},{"time":433000,"text":"You won't do that by accident; you will do that because you are guided to do that."},{"time":436000,"text":"Now we don't think that way."},{"time":438000,"text":"In the secular world we think, \"If an idea is important, I'll bump into it."},{"time":440000,"text":"I'll just come across it.\""},{"time":442000,"text":"Nonsense, says the religious world view."},{"time":444000,"text":"Religious view says we need calendars, we need to structure time,"},{"time":447000,"text":"we need to synchronize encounters."},{"time":449000,"text":"This comes across also"},{"time":451000,"text":"in the way in which religions set up rituals"},{"time":453000,"text":"around important feelings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455000,"text":"Take the Moon. It's really important to look at the Moon."},{"time":458000,"text":"You know, when you look at the Moon,"},{"time":460000,"text":"you think, \"I'm really small. What are my problems?\""},{"time":462000,"text":"It sets things into perspective, etc., etc."},{"time":464000,"text":"We should all look at the Moon a bit more often. We don't."},{"time":466000,"text":"Why don't we? Well there's nothing to tell us, \"Look at the Moon.\""},{"time":469000,"text":"But if you're a Zen Buddhist in the middle of September,"},{"time":472000,"text":"you will be ordered out of your home, made to stand on a canonical platform"},{"time":475000,"text":"and made to celebrate the festival of Tsukimi,"},{"time":477000,"text":"where you will be given poems to read"},{"time":479000,"text":"in honor of the Moon and the passage of time"},{"time":481000,"text":"and the frailty of life that it should remind us of."},{"time":483000,"text":"You'll be handed rice cakes."},{"time":485000,"text":"And the Moon and the reflection on the Moon"},{"time":487000,"text":"will have a secure place in your heart."},{"time":489000,"text":"That's very good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491000,"text":"The other thing that religions are really aware of"},{"time":493000,"text":"is: speak well --"},{"time":495000,"text":"I'm not doing a very good job of this here --"},{"time":497000,"text":"but oratory, oratory is absolutely key to religions."},{"time":500000,"text":"In the secular world, you can come through the university system and be a lousy speaker"},{"time":503000,"text":"and still have a great career."},{"time":505000,"text":"But the religious world doesn't think that way."},{"time":507000,"text":"What you're saying needs to be backed up"},{"time":509000,"text":"by a really convincing way of saying it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"So if you go to an African-American Pentecostalist church"},{"time":513000,"text":"in the American South"},{"time":515000,"text":"and you listen to how they talk,"},{"time":517000,"text":"my goodness, they talk well."},{"time":519000,"text":"After every convincing point, people will go, \"Amen, amen, amen.\""},{"time":522000,"text":"At the end of a really rousing paragraph, they'll all stand up,"},{"time":524000,"text":"and they'll go, \"Thank you Jesus, thank you Christ, thank you Savior.\""},{"time":527000,"text":"If we were doing it like they do it --"},{"time":529000,"text":"let's not do it, but if we were to do it --"},{"time":532000,"text":"I would tell you something like, \"Culture should replace scripture.\""},{"time":534000,"text":"And you would go, \"Amen, amen, amen.\""},{"time":536000,"text":"And at the end of my talk, you would all stand up"},{"time":538000,"text":"and you would go, \"Thank you Plato, thank you Shakespeare, thank you Jane Austen.\""},{"time":540000,"text":"And we'd know that we had a real rhythm going."},{"time":543000,"text":"All right, all right. We're getting there. We're getting there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":547000,"text":"The other thing that religions know is we're not just brains,"},{"time":549000,"text":"we are also bodies."},{"time":551000,"text":"And when they teach us a lesson,"},{"time":553000,"text":"they do it via the body."},{"time":555000,"text":"So for example,"},{"time":557000,"text":"take the Jewish idea of forgiveness."},{"time":559000,"text":"Jews are very interested in forgiveness"},{"time":561000,"text":"and how we should start anew and start afresh."},{"time":563000,"text":"They don't just deliver us sermons on this."},{"time":565000,"text":"They don't just give us books or words about this."},{"time":567000,"text":"They tell us to have a bath."},{"time":569000,"text":"So in Orthodox Jewish communities, every Friday you go to a Mikveh."},{"time":572000,"text":"You immerse yourself in the water,"},{"time":574000,"text":"and a physical action backs up a philosophical idea."},{"time":577000,"text":"We don't tend to do that."},{"time":579000,"text":"Our ideas are in one area and our behavior with our bodies is in another."},{"time":582000,"text":"Religions are fascinating in the way they try and combine the two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584000,"text":"Let's look at art now."},{"time":586000,"text":"Now art is something that in the secular world,"},{"time":589000,"text":"we think very highly of. We think art is really, really important."},{"time":592000,"text":"A lot of our surplus wealth goes to museums, etc."},{"time":595000,"text":"We sometimes hear it said"},{"time":597000,"text":"that museums are our new cathedrals, or our new churches."},{"time":600000,"text":"You've heard that saying."},{"time":602000,"text":"Now I think that the potential is there,"},{"time":604000,"text":"but we've completely let ourselves down."},{"time":606000,"text":"And the reason we've let ourselves down"},{"time":608000,"text":"is that we're not properly studying"},{"time":610000,"text":"how religions handle art."}]},{"cues":[{"time":614000,"text":"The two really bad ideas that are hovering in the modern world"},{"time":617000,"text":"that inhibit our capacity to draw strength from art:"},{"time":621000,"text":"The first idea is that art should be for art's sake --"},{"time":623000,"text":"a ridiculous idea --"},{"time":625000,"text":"an idea that art should live in a hermetic bubble"},{"time":627000,"text":"and should not try to do anything with this troubled world."},{"time":630000,"text":"I couldn't disagree more."},{"time":632000,"text":"The other thing that we believe is that art shouldn't explain itself,"},{"time":635000,"text":"that artists shouldn't say what they're up to,"},{"time":637000,"text":"because if they said it, it might destroy the spell"},{"time":639000,"text":"and we might find it too easy."},{"time":641000,"text":"That's why a very common feeling when you're in a museum --"},{"time":643000,"text":"let's admit it --"},{"time":645000,"text":"is, \"I don't know what this is about.\""},{"time":647000,"text":"But if we're serious people, we don't admit to that."},{"time":649000,"text":"But that feeling of puzzlement is structural"},{"time":652000,"text":"to contemporary art."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655000,"text":"Now religions have a much saner attitude to art."},{"time":657000,"text":"They have no trouble telling us what art is about."},{"time":659000,"text":"Art is about two things in all the major faiths."},{"time":661000,"text":"Firstly, it's trying to remind you"},{"time":663000,"text":"of what there is to love."},{"time":665000,"text":"And secondly, it's trying to remind you"},{"time":667000,"text":"of what there is to fear and to hate."},{"time":669000,"text":"And that's what art is."},{"time":671000,"text":"Art is a visceral encounter with the most important ideas of your faith."},{"time":674000,"text":"So as you walk around a church,"},{"time":676000,"text":"or a mosque or a cathedral,"},{"time":678000,"text":"what you're trying to imbibe, what you're imbibing is,"},{"time":680000,"text":"through your eyes, through your senses,"},{"time":682000,"text":"truths that have otherwise come to you through your mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684000,"text":"Essentially it's propaganda."},{"time":686000,"text":"Rembrandt is a propagandist"},{"time":688000,"text":"in the Christian view."},{"time":690000,"text":"Now the word \"propaganda\" sets off alarm bells."},{"time":692000,"text":"We think of Hitler, we think of Stalin. Don't, necessarily."},{"time":694000,"text":"Propaganda is a manner of being didactic in honor of something."},{"time":697000,"text":"And if that thing is good, there's no problem with it at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700000,"text":"My view is that museums should take a leaf out of the book of religions."},{"time":704000,"text":"And they should make sure that when you walk into a museum --"},{"time":706000,"text":"if I was a museum curator,"},{"time":708000,"text":"I would make a room for love, a room for generosity."},{"time":711000,"text":"All works of art are talking to us about things."},{"time":713000,"text":"And if we were able to arrange spaces"},{"time":715000,"text":"where we could come across works"},{"time":717000,"text":"where we would be told, use these works of art"},{"time":719000,"text":"to cement these ideas in your mind,"},{"time":721000,"text":"we would get a lot more out of art."},{"time":723000,"text":"Art would pick up the duty that it used to have"},{"time":726000,"text":"and that we've neglected because of certain mis-founded ideas."},{"time":729000,"text":"Art should be one of the tools"},{"time":731000,"text":"by which we improve our society."},{"time":733000,"text":"Art should be didactic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736000,"text":"Let's think of something else."},{"time":738000,"text":"The people in the modern world, in the secular world,"},{"time":740000,"text":"who are interested in matters of the spirit,"},{"time":742000,"text":"in matters of the mind,"},{"time":744000,"text":"in higher soul-like concerns,"},{"time":747000,"text":"tend to be isolated individuals."},{"time":749000,"text":"They're poets, they're philosophers, they're photographers, they're filmmakers."},{"time":752000,"text":"And they tend to be on their own."},{"time":754000,"text":"They're our cottage industries. They are vulnerable, single people."},{"time":757000,"text":"And they get depressed and they get sad on their own."},{"time":759000,"text":"And they don't really change much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761000,"text":"Now think about religions, think about organized religions."},{"time":763000,"text":"What do organized religions do?"},{"time":765000,"text":"They group together, they form institutions."},{"time":768000,"text":"And that has all sorts of advantages."},{"time":770000,"text":"First of all, scale, might."},{"time":773000,"text":"The Catholic Church pulled in 97 billion dollars last year"},{"time":776000,"text":"according to the Wall Street Journal."},{"time":778000,"text":"These are massive machines."},{"time":780000,"text":"They're collaborative, they're branded, they're multinational,"},{"time":783000,"text":"and they're highly disciplined."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785000,"text":"These are all very good qualities."},{"time":787000,"text":"We recognize them in relation to corporations."},{"time":789000,"text":"And corporations are very like religions in many ways,"},{"time":791000,"text":"except they're right down at the bottom of the pyramid of needs."},{"time":793000,"text":"They're selling us shoes and cars."},{"time":795000,"text":"Whereas the people who are selling us the higher stuff --"},{"time":797000,"text":"the therapists, the poets --"},{"time":799000,"text":"are on their own and they have no power,"},{"time":801000,"text":"they have no might."},{"time":803000,"text":"So religions are the foremost example"},{"time":806000,"text":"of an institution that is fighting for the things of the mind."},{"time":809000,"text":"Now we may not agree with what religions are trying to teach us,"},{"time":812000,"text":"but we can admire the institutional way"},{"time":814000,"text":"in which they're doing it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816000,"text":"Books alone, books written by lone individuals,"},{"time":819000,"text":"are not going to change anything."},{"time":821000,"text":"We need to group together."},{"time":823000,"text":"If you want to change the world, you have to group together, you have to be collaborative."},{"time":826000,"text":"And that's what religions do."},{"time":828000,"text":"They are multinational, as I say,"},{"time":830000,"text":"they are branded, they have a clear identity,"},{"time":833000,"text":"so they don't get lost in a busy world."},{"time":835000,"text":"That's something we can learn from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":837000,"text":"I want to conclude."},{"time":839000,"text":"Really what I want to say"},{"time":841000,"text":"is for many of you who are operating in a range of different fields,"},{"time":844000,"text":"there is something to learn from the example of religion --"},{"time":847000,"text":"even if you don't believe any of it."},{"time":850000,"text":"If you're involved in anything that's communal,"},{"time":852000,"text":"that involves lots of people getting together,"},{"time":854000,"text":"there are things for you in religion."},{"time":856000,"text":"If you're involved, say, in a travel industry in any way,"},{"time":859000,"text":"look at pilgrimage."},{"time":861000,"text":"Look very closely at pilgrimage."},{"time":863000,"text":"We haven't begun to scratch the surface"},{"time":865000,"text":"of what travel could be"},{"time":867000,"text":"because we haven't looked at what religions do with travel."},{"time":869000,"text":"If you're in the art world,"},{"time":871000,"text":"look at the example of what religions are doing with art."},{"time":873000,"text":"And if you're an educator in any way,"},{"time":876000,"text":"again, look at how religions are spreading ideas."},{"time":879000,"text":"You may not agree with the ideas,"},{"time":881000,"text":"but my goodness, they're highly effective mechanisms for doing so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884000,"text":"So really my concluding point"},{"time":886000,"text":"is you may not agree with religion,"},{"time":888000,"text":"but at the end of the day,"},{"time":890000,"text":"religions are so subtle, so complicated,"},{"time":892000,"text":"so intelligent in many ways"},{"time":894000,"text":"that they're not fit to be abandoned to the religious alone;"},{"time":897000,"text":"they're for all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":918000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Now this is actually a courageous talk,"},{"time":920000,"text":"because you're kind of setting up yourself in some ways"},{"time":922000,"text":"to be ridiculed in some quarters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":924000,"text":"AB: You can get shot by both sides."},{"time":926000,"text":"You can get shot by the hard-headed atheists,"},{"time":928000,"text":"and you can get shot by those who fully believe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931000,"text":"CA: Incoming missiles from North Oxford at any moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933000,"text":"AB: Indeed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":935000,"text":"CA: But you left out one aspect of religion"},{"time":938000,"text":"that a lot of people might say"},{"time":940000,"text":"your agenda could borrow from,"},{"time":942000,"text":"which is this sense --"},{"time":944000,"text":"that's actually probably the most important thing to anyone who's religious --"},{"time":946000,"text":"of spiritual experience,"},{"time":948000,"text":"of some kind of connection"},{"time":950000,"text":"with something that's bigger than you are."},{"time":952000,"text":"Is there any room for that experience in Atheism 2.0?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":955000,"text":"AB: Absolutely. I, like many of you, meet people"},{"time":958000,"text":"who say things like, \"But isn't there something bigger than us,"},{"time":961000,"text":"something else?\""},{"time":963000,"text":"And I say, \"Of course.\" And they say, \"So aren't you sort of religious?\""},{"time":966000,"text":"And I go, \"No.\" Why does that sense of mystery,"},{"time":969000,"text":"that sense of the dizzying scale of the universe,"},{"time":972000,"text":"need to be accompanied by a mystical feeling?"},{"time":975000,"text":"Science and just observation"},{"time":977000,"text":"gives us that feeling without it,"},{"time":979000,"text":"so I don't feel the need."},{"time":981000,"text":"The universe is large and we are tiny,"},{"time":983000,"text":"without the need for further religious superstructure."},{"time":987000,"text":"So one can have so-called spiritual moments"},{"time":989000,"text":"without belief in the spirit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":991000,"text":"CA: Actually, let me just ask a question."},{"time":993000,"text":"How many people here would say"},{"time":995000,"text":"that religion is important to them?"},{"time":999000,"text":"Is there an equivalent process"},{"time":1002000,"text":"by which there's a sort of bridge"},{"time":1004000,"text":"between what you're talking about and what you would say to them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007000,"text":"AB: I would say that there are many, many gaps in secular life"},{"time":1009000,"text":"and these can be plugged."},{"time":1011000,"text":"It's not as though, as I try to suggest,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"it's not as though either you have religion"},{"time":1015000,"text":"and then you have to accept all sorts of things,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"or you don't have religion"},{"time":1019000,"text":"and then you're cut off from all these very good things."},{"time":1022000,"text":"It's so sad that we constantly say,"},{"time":1025000,"text":"\"I don't believe so I can't have community,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"so I'm cut off from morality,"},{"time":1029000,"text":"so I can't go on a pilgrimage.\""},{"time":1031000,"text":"One wants to say, \"Nonsense. Why not?\""},{"time":1033000,"text":"And that's really the spirit of my talk."},{"time":1035000,"text":"There's so much we can absorb."},{"time":1037000,"text":"Atheism shouldn't cut itself off from the rich sources of religion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1040000,"text":"CA: It seems to me that there's plenty of people in the TED community"},{"time":1043000,"text":"who are atheists."},{"time":1045000,"text":"But probably most people in the community"},{"time":1047000,"text":"certainly don't think that religion is going away any time soon"},{"time":1050000,"text":"and want to find the language"},{"time":1052000,"text":"to have a constructive dialogue"},{"time":1055000,"text":"and to feel like we can actually talk to each other"},{"time":1057000,"text":"and at least share some things in common."},{"time":1059000,"text":"Are we foolish to be optimistic"},{"time":1061000,"text":"about the possibility of a world"},{"time":1063000,"text":"where, instead of religion being the great rallying cry"},{"time":1066000,"text":"of divide and war,"},{"time":1068000,"text":"that there could be bridging?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1070000,"text":"AB: No, we need to be polite about differences."},{"time":1073000,"text":"Politeness is a much-overlooked virtue."},{"time":1075000,"text":"It's seen as hypocrisy."},{"time":1077000,"text":"But we need to get to a stage when you're an atheist"},{"time":1079000,"text":"and someone says, \"Well you know, I did pray the other day,\""},{"time":1082000,"text":"you politely ignore it."},{"time":1084000,"text":"You move on."},{"time":1086000,"text":"Because you've agreed on 90 percent of things,"},{"time":1089000,"text":"because you have a shared view on so many things,"},{"time":1091000,"text":"and you politely differ."},{"time":1093000,"text":"And I think that's what the religious wars of late have ignored."},{"time":1097000,"text":"They've ignored the possibility of harmonious disagreement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1101000,"text":"CA: And finally, does this new thing that you're proposing"},{"time":1103000,"text":"that's not a religion but something else,"},{"time":1105000,"text":"does it need a leader,"},{"time":1107000,"text":"and are you volunteering to be the pope?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1109000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1111000,"text":"AB: Well, one thing that we're all very suspicious of"},{"time":1113000,"text":"is individual leaders."},{"time":1115000,"text":"It doesn't need it."},{"time":1117000,"text":"What I've tried to lay out is a framework"},{"time":1119000,"text":"and I'm hoping that people can just fill it in."},{"time":1122000,"text":"I've sketched a sort of broad framework."},{"time":1124000,"text":"But wherever you are, as I say, if you're in the travel industry, do that travel bit."},{"time":1127000,"text":"If you're in the communal industry, look at religion and do the communal bit."},{"time":1130000,"text":"So it's a wiki project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1132000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1134000,"text":"CA: Alain, thank you for sparking many conversations later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1137000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}